🎶On the 1st day of Xmas, Universal gifted me… 
A DEDICATION TO CARL LAEMMLE🎶

🎞️ 
To kick off  #12DaysofUniversalMonsters here on UMU, we’re showing our monster love and appreciation to the one and only Carl Laemmle Sr. and his son Carl Jr. 

🎞️ 
Simply put, there would be no Universal if not for these fine gentlemen. 
Starting off as a collection of various film studios coming together as the “Universal Film Manufacturing Company” in 1912, the Laemmle’s were truly the catalyst to what would become one of the biggest household names in film and motion picture history, let alone, horror history.

🎞️
Though they may no longer be with us, their legacy lives on in more and more Universal movies being created, frequent park visitors, and on the monsters side, by Laemmle’s niece @antoniacarlotta . 
If you haven’t seen her website or watched her YouTube series “Universally Me” you’re truly missing out!! We appreciate you Antonia, thank you for keeping your Uncle’s (and the Monsters) legacy alive forever🖤

🎄 Follow along to see the rest of the 12 Days and see what Universal will bring us next!🎁

Happy Holidays #MonsterFam and Creeps!☠️❄️🎅🕎

This is going to be a great party for art lovers and horror lovers. I've said many times, that @jeremysaffer is the architect of my reinvention. These photos changed everything for me.  So thrilled for his achievement & to have been a part of it.  Very proud and pleased to call him my friend and mentor.  I will be there to celebrate this show and sign ~ Tomorrow, a dream come true for me, as my first Los Angeles gallery show happens (at Exhibit A gallery). As a project that has meant so much to me and taken up a third of my lifetime is finally seen as physical singular art pieces as well as celebrating the book. This project is one that many run away from, dont understand, and are still scared of touching. When you meet like minded artists such as Tyson who believed in the book and turned the project into a physical art collection, and Richard who saw the work and wanted to have it on display at his amazing gallery, it gives so much validity to all the work that went into this project not just from me but also the many incredible powerful women who are a part of it. Walking up to the gallery yesterday and seeing the giant window displays, the daughters logos and displays was an emotional and affirming moment for me to say the least, I was blown away by what they are doing to make this show so special. I am hoping to see as many friends, fans, family, and more possible at the show tomorrow night. Please come by and hang out. Its at Exhibit A Gallery in Los Angeles 6pm til Midnight. Come celebrate with me as this dream becomes as reality and you can even see all new work for Daughters of Darkness I have done the past two years since the book was released. I will be doing a book signing, there are 1/1 large art pieces, a super limited (only 10!) collab piece with Richard, and tons of Daughters of Darkness surprises. I hope to see as many of you there as possible.

@thehorrorjunkee Good afternoon and happy Friday everyone! Hope everyone’s weekend is starting out great! So today I wanted to look back at a film that I don’t hear many people talk about which is a real shame, because I really enjoyed this one, and that is 2013s ‘Contracted’ not the easiest one to watch, but I really enjoyed the story and where it all ended up at which I was totally not expecting throughout the whole film. Great performance by Najarra Townsend ( @najarra ) as the lead role Samantha, and of course I always LOVE seeing the beautiful and talented Caroline Williams (@willicaroline ) on screen, and she does a good job playing Samantha’s mom. Long story short, recovering addict goes to friends party, accepts a drink from a stranger who had just done some very questionable things before going to the party, and the drink was drugged, and Samantha ends up getting raped in this guys car. Unfortunately, this is the least of her worries after her body basically starts deteriorating. Like I said I did not see the ending coming and I don’t want to spoil or give anything away. All I can say is I definitely recommend this one and highly suggest you go check it out!

‘Contracted’ (2013)
Director: Eric England
Starring: Najarra Townsend, Caroline Williams, Alice Macdonald and Matt Mercer

Posted @withregram • @jase_marsiglia Ten Minutes to Midnight (2020) The great #CarolineWilliams returns to the DJ booth, as popular heavy metal DJ Amy Marlow, who’s facing being “aged out” of her position by a younger gal (#NicoleKang). Rightfully bitter, Amy “signs off” in style before biting – yes, BITING – the new girl, Sienna. As a storm that’s whipping into a hurricane barricades the midnight crew into the studio for the night, Amy must confront some harsh truths and some alarming changes after a bite on the neck by “something” outside earlier. 
.
#TenMinutestoMidnight is a cerebral metaphor on ageism, using vampirism as its trojan horse. At the center is Williams, in a career-defining performance. Director/Co-Writer #ErikBloomquist asks a hell of a lot in this role which requires Williams to spiral into madness, sadness, anger, pain, and confusion – and she proves she’s more than up to the task. Amy’s “transformation” forces her to look at herself not as a simple victim, but as an aged product being pushed aside for the “new model” (doubly ironic considering the already-sexy Williams has never looked MORE luminous). 
.
Williams brings forth something immeasurably different from anything she’s done prior, and it’s magnetic and exciting to watch. She has moments of true menace here, as the horror elements are present, but the moments where she exudes jealousy of youth and sexuality, or her fear of “change” are what’s most engaging, moving and heartbreaking. Amy was objectified by her manager when she was young, just like her contemporary now – is she sickened by it, or secretly jealous of it? Williams doesn’t give us an easy interpretation. 
.
She’s also turning into “something else” and she’s frightened. Whether it’s a blood-sucking vampire or a simply a woman that society has deemed “past her prime”, she’s understandably terrified and feels betrayed by people she considered her friends who could have warned her, and a clock that won’t stop ticking towards that final hour. There’s so much more to get done, so many things unfinished, and Amy just isn’t ready. Are any of us? ⭐⭐⭐1/2 out of ⭐⭐⭐⭐.
